title: Torsten Raspe
text:
Torsten Raspe (born 1 August 1969) is a retired <a href="Germany">German</a> <a href="Association%20football">football</a> <a href="midfielder">midfielder</a> who played for <a href="Hallescher%20FC">Hallescher FC Chemie</a>, <a href="SSV%20Ulm%201846">SSV Ulm 1846</a>, <a href="Stuttgarter%20Kickers">Stuttgarter Kickers</a>, <a href="Rot-Wei%C3%9F%20Erfurt">Rot-Weiß Erfurt</a> and <a href="VfL%20Kirchheim/Teck">VfL Kirchheim/Teck</a>.
He was a part of the East German squad at the <a href="1989%20FIFA%20World%20Youth%20Championship">1989 FIFA World Youth Championship</a>, playing all three matches.
